The course will give an overview of how complex conceptual categories as personhood, kinship, gift exchange, language, ethics and some others have been developed and are currently used in ethnology/anthropology. Students will have to read landmark texts that have significantly influenced the discipline recently.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course will introduce conceptual thinking and its dynamics in contemporary ethnology/anthropology. The focus will be upon particular concepts and epistemological issues, which have significantly influenced ethnological/anthropological thought and writing today.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the course, students will be able to analyse key concepts in ethnology/anthropology from different perspectives born in ongoing theoretical debates. Students will acquire an ability to read topical ethnographies and use the concepts independently in their own writings.
